               <msContents>
                  <summary>Apollonios orders Zenon to plant fir-trees all over the park and round the vineyard and the olive-groves, in the number of at least three hundred.  For the tree has a striking appearance and will be of service to the king.  That is to say, it would provide timber for ship-building besides being an ornament to the estate.</summary>
